hînkirin, em jî wan hînî.
 
Our dance group had teachers. Maybe some are not here, some
are in Afrin, some stayed in Aleppo, they dispersed. They
taught us, and we taught others.

108
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:47,000
Ê naha ez bizanim niha eldaf wisa tiştek ji koma reqsê dûr
e. Yanî wisa rîtm heve lê.
 
Now I want to know, currently the tambourine is somewhat
different from the dance group. Meaning they have rhythm
but.

109
00:08:47,000 --> 00:08:58,000
Bixwedê nêzîkî gen da ko eldaf îqa' e. Meselen nuha koma
reqsê destpêkê yanî kesek bixwaze koma reqsê, esas îqa'ê xwe
bigere. Îqa'a zanibe.
 
By God, they are close because the tambourine is rhythm. For
example, now a dance group initially, if someone wants a
dance group, the basis is to find the rhythm. They must know
the rhythm.

110
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:05,000
Nuha def em belkî grûp yanî gine giştî be, sê çar bi xwe
defê meselen dest xwe kin defê li da'weta lêxistin e.
 
Now the tambourine, maybe we as a general group, three or
four people take the tambourines and play them at weddings.

111
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:12,000
Li da'weta te îqa' girtin, meselen te çi defê te çi îqa'ê
dest xwe kir me rîkone di herêm da, lêxin e.
 
At the weddings you caught the rhythm, for example whatever
tambourine or rhythm you picked up in the region, play it.

112
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:16,000
Tab'en ji îqa'a de ha. Te bîr der je bo dûr e. Meselen eldaf
durbek yanî bi dest me keda, î govenda dikê, îqa'a xwe bigrê
kanê lêxin. Erê zanibe.
 
Of course it comes from the rhythm. You might think it is
far. For example, playing the tambourine with our hands
while doing the dance, catching the rhythm to play. Yes,
they must know.

113
00:09:16,000 --> 00:09:21,000
Yanî ev tiştekî ji me va nêzîk bû, em hawa zû hîn bûn, û te
delîl nexêr e.
 
Meaning, this was close to us, we learned it quickly, and
there is no lack of proof.

114
00:09:21,000 --> 00:09:25,000
Welleh kekê Ehmed em pir kêf xweş ne. Ev tiştkî nû em
dibînin niha ecêb e.
 
By God brother Ahmed, we are very happy. This new thing we
are seeing is amazing.

115
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:30,000
Berî vê sê-çar dawetên we dîtî, tiştekî xweş e. Û millet pir
kêfxweş dibin pê.
 
Before this, we saw three or four of your weddings, it's
something beautiful. And the people are very happy with it.

116
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:34,000
Pir kêfxweş e, erê, tiştekî ecêb e, menzere nû derbaz
da'weta bîye.
 
It is very pleasing, yes, it's a wonderful thing, a new
scene has entered the weddings.

117
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:38,000
Em sipasiya we dikin xwişkê Axîn. Sipasiya we hemîya dikin.
 
We thank you, sister Akhin. We thank you all.

118
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:46,000
Dema hûn der tên dawetan, kî stranê ji we ra îxtiyar dike?
Hûn ji ku tînin vê stranê?
 
When you go out to weddings, who chooses the songs for you?
Where do you bring these songs from?

119
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:50,000
Bixwe em bi xêrhatina we dikin. Bixêrhatina qenala Hatim Li
Efrînê dikin.
 
To begin with, we welcome you. We welcome the Hatim Li Efrîn
channel.

120
00:09:50,000 --> 00:09:56,000
Ji xwe stran em îxtiyar dikin. Em dixwazin yanî filklorê me
bêtir pêşê da be.
 
We choose the songs ourselves. We want our folklore to be
more advanced.

121
00:09:56,000 --> 00:09:59,000
Yanî wextê em dibînin bûk û zêva, reqsî sila da direqisin.
 
Meaning when we see the bride and groom dancing the
traditional dance.

122
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,000
Em jî ew kêlîka pir xweş, bi stranan dixemilînin.
 
We decorate that very beautiful moment with songs.

123
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:02,000
Û yanî na çendî me ye...
 
And I mean, it doesn't matter how long it has been for us...

124
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:05,000
yanî hene kêm ji çanda xwe dûr dikevin
 
I mean, there are some who slightly distance themselves from
their culture.

125
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:10,000
lê em wextê em bi çanda xwe derdikevin û filoklora xwe pêşî
miletî dikin, ku li me sêr dikin...
 
But when we present our culture and perform our folklore in
front of the people watching us...

126
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:13,000
ew pir xweş dibe, yanî filoklora me jî bi nav û deng dibe,
 
it becomes very beautiful. I mean, our folklore also becomes
famous.

127
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:21,000
û ev stranên ha stranên kurdî ne, em dixwazin stranên meyên
bav û kalan, em nû bikin. Ji nû ve biafirînin, yanî.
 
And these songs are Kurdish songs. We want to renew the
songs of our ancestors. To recreate them, I mean.

128
00:10:21,000 --> 00:10:27,000
Ji xwe em ji wê tunî der têne dawetan, yanî tiştekî jî xweş
e û ji bo me yanî serbilindî ye,
 
Actually, this is why we come out to weddings. I mean, it is
something beautiful and a source of pride for us,

129
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:31,000
yanî serbilindî ye, em dixwazin hîn filoklora xwe bidin
pêş...
 
I mean, a source of pride. We want to continue bringing our
folklore forward...

130
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:38,000
û bibe ku zêdetir zanibin filoklora me ev e, yanî da tiştên
ne filoklora me bin...
 
and maybe make it more known that this is our folklore, so
that things that are not our folklore...

131
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:41,000
Xwişkê Axîn, ez dixwazim di vir de tiştekî bizanibim,
 
Sister Axin, I want to know something here,

132
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:45,000
niha her tiştek, gava carekê derket sahe, em pê ne dibên.
 
right now, everything, when it comes onto the scene for the
first time, we say we are aware of it.

133
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:50,000
Wekî tiştekê neqdeyekî li dijî jî heye û rexneyek li dijî jî
heye, lê belê...
 
It has both its critics and its supporters, but...

134
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:58,000
ji ber ku, heta kesê bi wê dawetê hazir dibe, yavaş yavaş
heta dihêle ku niha berê em diçûn dawetên me berê li ser
bêderan bûn, bi def û zirne bûn,
 
because, even the person who attends that wedding, slowly
gets used to it. In the past, we used to go to our weddings
on the threshing floors, with a drum and zurna.

135
00:10:58,000 --> 00:10:59,000
ew tişt niha pir tinebûn.
 
Those things don't exist much anymore.

136
00:10:59,000 --> 00:11:05,000
Niha em dawetên me, gelek sal in ev tişt jî ecêb dîtin, xweş
e, pêşkêşiyek e ji miletê me yê efrînî ra,
 
Now, for many years, we have found these things strange in
our weddings. It is nice, a presentation for our Afrin
people.

137
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:17,000
bas di vir de em dixwazin bibînin, xwişkê Axîn, rojeke bibe
hûn daxwazin, keçikên we efrînkî, bi fîstanên we efrînkî, wa
cilkirinên dayîkên me yên berê, hûn ê wan tiştên rengîn jî
îdafe bikin li ciyê xwe?
 
But here we want to see, Sister Axin, one day will you want
your Afrin girls, in your Afrin dresses, in the traditional
clothes of our mothers from the past, to add those colorful
things to yourselves?

138
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:21,000
Erê rast e, ji xwe fîstanên me fîstanên efrînkî yê sêcefan
e,
 
Yes, that's true. Actually, our dresses are the Afrin se-cef
dresses.

139
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:28,000
yanî bi xwe evna fîstanên, ew jî yên kurdî ne, bes ê efrînkî
bi xwe tên nasîn, yanî fîstanên sêcef,
 
I mean, these dresses themselves are also Kurdish, but the
Afrin ones are recognized by themselves. I mean, the se-cef
dresses.

140
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:30,000
yê dayîkên me xwe dikirin, şar diştandin.
 
The ones our mothers used to wear, tying a scarf.

141
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:34,000
Demên pêş de inşellah, em ê bi van fîstanan derkevin.
 
In the future, God willing, we will perform in those
dresses.

142
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,000
Em hêvî ne.
 
We hope so.

143
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:44,000
Xwişkê Axîn ez dixwazim tiştekî din jî bizanibim, wextê hûn
derdikevin dawetê, gavê ku derî vedibe û zava werin li salê
û hûn derdikevin, hûn dest pê dikin,
 
Sister Axin, I want to know something else too. When you go
out to the wedding, when the door opens and the groom enters
the hall, and you come out and start,

144
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:48,000
wekî niha ji laxtokên ku karê we jî...
 
like now, from the moments of your work...

145
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:57,000
kesê li we temaşe dike, çi dibînin wextê berî bûk û zava
dakevin salê, hûn dest pê dikin, kesê li wê dawetê hazir
dibe li pêşî wî ra dibe ew hal?
 
what do the people watching you feel when you start before
the bride and groom come down to the hall? How does the
person attending that wedding react to that situation at
first?

146
00:11:57,000 --> 00:12:00,000
Yanî ji xwe dema em derdikevin dawetê, ev tiştek...
 
I mean, naturally, when we go out to the wedding, this is
something...

147
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:03,000
Eynî cara yekem li efrînê em derketin...
 
The very first time we performed in Afrin...

148
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:08,000
milet ecêb ma, yanî hîn kesî em nedîtibûn,
 
people were surprised. I mean, nobody had seen us yet.

149
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:16,000
yanî bi defê û bi vî fîstanî kesî yanî em nedîtibûn, dema em
derketin jî, milet ecêb ma...
 
I mean, nobody had seen us with the drum and this dress.
When we came out, the people were amazed...

150
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:22,000
Bes tiştekî pir xweş e, dema miletê me tiştekî bibîne û
tiştek ecêb di efrînê de çêbibe,
 
But it's something very beautiful when our people see
something and something extraordinary happens in Afrin.

151
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:27,000
yanî bi xwe efrîn, bi her tiştî tê nasîn, yanî em jî
dixwazin efrîniyên me, bi her tiştî werin nasîn.
 
I mean, Afrin itself is known for everything. So, we also
want our Afrin people to be known for everything.

152
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:30,000
Wallahî spas ji we ra, serkeftin ji we ra, û ji we ra û hemî
miletê kurd.
 
By God, thank you. Success to you, and to you, and to all
the Kurdish people.

153
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:31,000
Spas...
 
Thank you...

154
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:40,000
Birayê Silêman, em spasiya te dikin, wextê ku hûn derdikevin
dawetan, çi qas meblaxt tên ser vê karê dibin?
 
Brother Suleiman, we thank you. When you perform at
weddings, how much money goes into this work?

155
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:42,000
Rast bêjim ji bo te, xwişkê...
 
To tell you the truth, sister...

156
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:45,000
xwe em derdikevin dawetê...
 
actually, we perform at the wedding...

157
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:47,000
Hedefê me bi xwe ne pere ye...
 
Our goal itself is not money...

158
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:51,000
Belkî em qisme biçûk em jê dibin, ew jî wekî tu dîtî...
 
We might take a small portion of it, and that's just like
you saw...

159
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:56,000
ji pêdiviya xwe re, me mesarîf, pere derbaz dibe yanî,
 
for our needs, we have expenses, money is spent. I mean,

160
00:12:56,000 --> 00:13:00,000
meselê, em radibin ji derên me, masraf ji me ra, bas yanî
mesarîfê me, derdixin herin...
 
for example, we leave from our places, there are expenses
for us. But I mean, it just covers our expenses to go.

161
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:06,000
pêşînda em ne wisa, hedefê me tiştên wiha Efrînî pêşxistin,
 
Primarily, we are not like that, our goal is to promote
Afrin-like things,

162
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:09,000
kurdî pêşxistin, hedefê me ji wê zêdeye ku pere derîne.
 
to promote Kurdish culture. Our goal is more than just
making money.

163
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:19,000
em dixwazin tiştên wiha pêşxistin. Weseleyê pere der jî min
gotî, me mesarîf xira dikin, belkî em qismekê ji dibin mîne
ji em bi karan xwe pêbikin, ne ji armanca me pere ye, me bi
armanc pê kirin.
 
We want to promote such things. Regarding making money, as I
said, we cover our expenses. Maybe we take a part to
continue our work, not that our goal is money. We do it with
a purpose.

164
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:24,000
Ez tişt fêm dikim, ku dibêjin tiştekî basît wek di be...
 
I understand. You're saying it's a simple amount. Like
it's...

165
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:27,000
Ji bo mesrûfê xwe derxin bi maşîneyê...
 
To cover your expenses for the car...

166
00:13:27,000 --> 00:13:28,000
Em spasîya te dikin.
 
We thank you.

167
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:30,000
Spas xweş. Saq bin.
 
You're welcome. Stay healthy.

168
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:32,000
Xwişkê, di dawiyê ez dixwazim tiştekî zanibim...
 
Sister, finally, I want to know something...

169
00:13:32,000 --> 00:13:36,000
di vê karî de hûn dikin careke pir xweş, inşellah serkeftin
ji we re.
 
In this work you do, which is very beautiful, God willing,
success to you.

170
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:39,000
Tiştên herî bişî de vê karî de û tiştên na wextê çi ye?
 
What are the most beautiful things in this work, and what
are the bad things?

171
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:45,000
Destpêkê, em pir kêfxweş bûn. Ez bi vê tiştî ez dexet
dibînim. Tiştek foloklorî em dikin. Tiştekî xweş e...
 
At first, we were very happy. I pay attention to this. We
are doing something folkloric. It's a beautiful thing...

172
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:52,000
Tiştê xweş em foklora xwe em radibin yanî, bi xweş e, keç û
xortên me foklora xwe radibin, foloklora xwe bîr nakin.
 
The beautiful thing is that we are keeping our folklore
alive. It's nice, our young girls and boys are keeping their
folklore alive, they are not forgetting it.

173
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:56,000
Silavek me heye keça xorta me kurdan...
 
We have a greeting for our young Kurdish men and women...

174
00:13:56,000 --> 00:14:02,000
fa bila ber hunerê xwe werin, yanî, ber folklore xwe,
fêrnakin. Bilheks, na tiştek e ewe...
 
they should come to their art, to their folklore, not
neglect it. On the contrary, it's not a bad thing...

175
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:06,000
inşellah em kêfxweş e, bi sarê xwe bilind e, inşellah wê
folklor de pêş ve dixe...
 
God willing, we are happy, proud, and hopefully folklore
will advance...

176
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:10,000
pa vê silavê min ji keçê we xortê ma kurda ye...
 
so this is my greeting to our young Kurdish men and women...

177
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:14,000
Niha dengkirina me pir xweş e, dengkirina we pir xweş e, em
pir hezdikin em baweriyê xwe pê didin,
 
Now, our conversation is very nice, your conversation is
very nice. We love it very much and we put our trust in it.

178
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:17,000
em niha diçin destpêkê
 
We are going to the beginning now.

179
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:22,000
Inşellah em diçin dema we, deng û xebatê we, inşellah em
destpêdikin...
 
God willing, we will go to your time, your voice and work,
God willing we will start...

180
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:25,000
yalla em derên...
 
Yalla, let's go...

